The DCSE has announced a brand new online shares trading platform, which allows you to purchase shares of companies on the DCSE, from anywhere in the world, instead of visiting the trading hall in person.
This is not the first time the idea has been suggested, but it does appear that it is the first to resonate well with the average Yuppie using "the computer" to check stock prices.

When asked about security, Standard Financial Exchange Corp. claimed that they had hired "professional software engineers from Search.com" who "assured [them] that the best encryption in the world was used in [their product]."

Whether this is a long-term trend or just a fad will be down to the reader's interpretation, and only the future can tell us the real answer.
